data.description: Southern charm flows like honey from this stately home and welcomes you to experience all it has to offer.  Formerly known as ''Brookmore'', this 4 bedroom, 3 bath home is located on 3.10 acres.  The first floor offers a vast living room with new gas log fireplace, billiard room and den with warm wood paneled walls and full updated bath. The completely remodeled kitchen with breakfast area lends access to the laundry room, new walk in pantry and coffee bar.  Conveniently located off the kitchen is the formal dining room.  Enjoy reading in the cozy sunroom or relaxing & entertaining on the spacious screened in verandah. The grand stairway leads to a landing with 4 bedrooms and 2 baths with updates. Master bedroom has been reconfigured to allow more closet space and open up access to a hidden window for more sunlight. Secure vehicles and equipment in the 2 car detached garage and storage area.  Unfinished basement for additional storage.  Enjoy the summer nights on the swings on the side covered porch or roasting marshmallows around the firepit.  Plenty of privacy and beautiful landscaping with new retaining walls and outdoor decor. Circle driveway. Conveniently located into town or to Cherokee Lake, medical and shopping.  Buyer to verify all information to their satisfaction.  3rd fireplace not functional. Propane tank leased for $75.00 per year.
